    {
      "id": "64d78e33_26c4cb9c",
      "file_path": "docker-compose/docker-compose.yml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 211,
      "message": "NB: Our docker-compose.yml file has grown significantly, making it harder to maintain and understand. Here are some strategies to split and organize it effectively but as a part of seperate JITA task:\n\n\nExample Structure:\n\ndocker-compose/\n│── docker-compose.base.yml       # Common services (database, nginx, kafka, zookeeper)\n│── docker-compose.cps.yml        # CPS-related services\n│── docker-compose.dmi.yml        # DMI-related services\n│── docker-compose.sdnc.yml       # SDNC-related services\n│── docker-compose.override.yml   # Optional overrides for local development\n\n\nProfiles are already being used (dmi-service, dmi-stub, monitoring, etc.), but they can be structured better.\n\nCreate a base profile for essential services (dbpostgresql, nginx, kafka, zookeeper).\nDefine feature-specific profiles (dmi-service, cps, sdnc).\nUse overrides for testing if required.\n\n\n(Can be discussed with team)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2025-03-18 11:54:40.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "aedbf371_562ddfa4",
      "unresolved": true
    },
